    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-04T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="324"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–444</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss> to President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-04">April 4,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I enclose for your information and consideration a copy of a letter<note n="10"
                        xml:id="d324fn10">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                    </note> which I am forwarding to the Secretary of War commenting upon a proposal
                    by General Stilwell, concurred in by Ambassador Gauss, that you send a message
                    to the Generalissimo urging his assent to the dispatch immediately of a military
                    observers’ mission to the so-called Communist area in China.<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d324fn11">President Roosevelt indicated his approval and on April 5
                        returned to the Secretary of State the initialed copy of his letter to the
                        Secretary of War.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
